Project Assignment A: An explanation of the central idea behind your final project, e.g. think about questions such as

What is the idea? Investigating mental health data

Which datasets do you need to explore the idea? Surveys from different countries and also statistics from countries

Why is it interesting? Mental health is a developing issue and is very prevelent today

A mock up of the visualization that you wish to build. (Anything is fine here. Pen and paper, MS Paint, Inkscape, D3, Midjourney (or any other LLM), anything is OK). Map

Make sure you answer the questions

What genre is it? (for Genres, see section 4.3 of the Segel and Heer paper) Magazine style

Why is that genre right for telling the story you want to communicate with the data Because there are alot of underlying reasons for mental health problems that can best be explained with a text and visualization combo

A walk-through of your preliminary data-analysis, addressing What is the total size of your data? (MB, number of rows, number of variables, etc) 4MB ish, 48 thousand rows ish, 44 variables

What are other properties? (What is the date range? Is is it geo-data?, then a quick plot of locations, etc.) 1800-2017, Geo Data of most of the world (some countries missing like countries in Africa)

Show the fundamental distributions of the data (similar to the work we did on SF crime data)

from ipywidgets import interact, Dropdown


# Aggregate data by country and year
grouped_data = prev_mental_subst.groupby(['entity', 'year'])['depression'].mean().reset_index()

def update_plot(year):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))  # Adjust figure size as needed
    filtered_data = grouped_data[grouped_data['year'] == year]
    filtered_data = filtered_data.sort_values(by='depression', ascending=False)

    # Extract the country with the highest and lowest depression prevalence
    highest_country = filtered_data.iloc[0]['entity']
    highest_value = filtered_data.iloc[0]['depression']

    lowest_country = filtered_data.iloc[-1]['entity']
    lowest_value = filtered_data.iloc[-1]['depression']

    # Create a bar plot for all countries
    bars = plt.bar(filtered_data['entity'], filtered_data['depression'], color='skyblue')

    # Highlight bars for highest and lowest values
    for bar in bars:
        if bar.get_height() == highest_value:
            bar.set_color('skyblue')
        elif bar.get_height() == lowest_value:
            bar.set_color('skyblue')

    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Depression Prevalence')
    plt.title(f'Depression Prevalence in {year}')

    # Customize x-axis labels to display only highest and lowest countries
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=12)
    labels = plt.gca().get_xticklabels()
    for label in labels:
        if label.get_text() not in [highest_country, lowest_country]:
            label.set_visible(False)

    plt.tight_layout()  # Adjust layout to prevent clipping of labels
    plt.show()



# Get unique years
years = grouped_data['year'].unique()

# Create a dropdown widget
year_dropdown = Dropdown(options=years, description='Year:')

# Display the interactive plot
interact(update_plot, year=year_dropdown)

def update_plot(year):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    filtered_data = grouped_data[grouped_data['year'] == year]
    filtered_data = filtered_data.sort_values(by='depression', ascending=False)

    highest_country = filtered_data.iloc[0]['entity']
    highest_value = filtered_data.iloc[0]['depression']

    lowest_country = filtered_data.iloc[-1]['entity']
    lowest_value = filtered_data.iloc[-1]['depression']

    bars = plt.bar(filtered_data['entity'], filtered_data['depression'], color='skyblue')

    for bar in bars:
        if bar.get_height() == highest_value:
            bar.set_color('orange')  # Highlight highest value
        elif bar.get_height() == lowest_value:
            bar.set_color('yellow')  # Highlight lowest value

    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Depression Prevalence')
    plt.title(f'Depression Prevalence in {year}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=12)

    labels = plt.gca().get_xticklabels()
    for label in labels:
        if label.get_text() not in [highest_country, lowest_country]:
            label.set_visible(False)

    plt.tight_layout()

    # Save the plot as a PNG file
    plt.savefig(f"/content/drive/MyDrive/depression_prevalence_{year}.png")

    plt.show()

# Define age groups
age_groups = ['10-14', '15-19', '20-24', '25-29', '30-34', '15-49', '50-69', '70']

values = prev_dep_age_greenland_2017.iloc[:, 3:].values.flatten()

# Get the index of the age group with the highest prevalence
max_index = np.argmax(values)

# Create a list of colors (gray for all age groups except the highest)
colors = ['gray'] * len(age_groups)
colors[max_index] = 'red'

# Plot the bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(age_groups, values, color=colors)
plt.xlabel('Age Groups')
plt.ylabel('Prevalence of Depression')
plt.title('Prevalence of depression across different age groups in Greenland (2017)')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Filter the DataFrame for a specific year
year = 2017  # Replace with the year you want to visualize
prev_mental_subst_2017 = prev_mental_subst[prev_mental_subst['year'] == year]
prev_mental_subst_2017_dep = prev_mental_subst_2017[['entity','depression']]
prev_mental_subst_2017_alc = prev_mental_subst_2017[['entity','alcohol_use_disorders']]

# Extract data for Greenland
greenland_data_dep = prev_mental_subst_2017_dep[prev_mental_subst_2017['entity'] == 'Greenland']['depression']
greenland_data_alc = prev_mental_subst_2017_alc[prev_mental_subst_2017['entity'] == 'Greenland']['alcohol_use_disorders']

# Scatter plot
plt.scatter(prev_mental_subst_2017_dep['depression'], prev_mental_subst_2017_alc['alcohol_use_disorders'], label='Other Countries')
plt.scatter(greenland_data_dep, greenland_data_alc, color='red', label='Greenland', marker='o')

plt.xlabel('Depression')
plt.ylabel('Drug Use Disorders')
plt.title('Scatter plot of Depression vs Drug Use Disorders in 2017')
plt.legend()

# Calculate correlation coefficient
correlation = np.corrcoef(prev_mental_subst_2017_dep['depression'], prev_mental_subst_2017_alc['alcohol_use_disorders'])[0, 1]
print(f'Correlation coefficient: {correlation}')

plt.show()

greenland_alcohol = greenland_data[['year', 'alcohol_use_disorders']]

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Drug consumption
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)

plt.plot(european_drug.index, european_drug.values, label='European Countries', marker='x')
plt.title('Drug Use Disorders')

plt.ylabel('Level')
plt.legend()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# Sample datasets (replace with your actual datasets)
# suicide_vs_prev = pd.read_csv('suicide_vs_prev.csv')
# prev_mental_subst = pd.read_csv('prev_mental_subst.csv')

# Convert 'year' column to numeric type, replacing non-numeric values with NaN
suicide_vs_prev['year'] = pd.to_numeric(suicide_vs_prev['year'], errors='coerce')

# Drop rows where 'year' is NaN
suicide_vs_prev.dropna(subset=['year'], inplace=True)

# Convert 'year' column to integer type
suicide_vs_prev['year'] = suicide_vs_prev['year'].astype(int)

# Filter suicide_vs_prev dataframe for years >= 1990
suicide_vs_prev_filtered = suicide_vs_prev[suicide_vs_prev['year'] >= 1990]

# Concatenate the dataframes based on 'year' and 'entity' columns
combined_data = pd.merge(suicide_vs_prev_filtered, prev_mental_subst, on=['year', 'entity'])

# Filter the data for Greenland
greenland_data = combined_data[combined_data['entity'] == 'Greenland']

# Extract required columns
greenland_data = greenland_data[['year', 'suicide_rate_deaths_per_100_000_individuals', 'depression', 'alcohol_use_disorders', 'drug_use_disorders']]

# Scatter plot and correlation calculation for each pair of variables
variables = ['depression', 'alcohol_use_disorders', 'drug_use_disorders']
for var in variables:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(greenland_data[var], greenland_data['suicide_rate_deaths_per_100_000_individuals'])
    plt.xlabel(var.capitalize())
    plt.ylabel('Suicide Rate (deaths per 100,000 individuals)')
    plt.title(f'Scatter plot of {var.capitalize()} vs Suicide Rate in Greenland')

    # Calculate correlation coefficient
    correlation = np.corrcoef(greenland_data[var], greenland_data['suicide_rate_deaths_per_100_000_individuals'])[0, 1]
    print(f'Correlation coefficient between {var.capitalize()} and Suicide Rate: {correlation}')

    plt.show()
